    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-11-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-11-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="40"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d40">
                <head>40. Memorandum From Acting Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_JUA1"
                        type="from">Johnson</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_NRM1"
                        type="to">Nixon</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d40fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Executive Secretariat, Conference Files:
                        Lot 70 D 387, Box 522, Volume II, <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>
                        Ministerial, Dec. 2–4. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1970-11-27">November 27, 1970</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Positions to be Taken at December Ministerial Meetings</item>
                </list>
                <p>We were informed in <gloss target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss> 95 of November 25<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d40fn2">
                        <gloss target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss> 95, “<gloss target="#t_US1"
                            >U.S.</gloss> Strategy and Forces for <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                            >NATO</gloss>,” November 25, stated with regard to <gloss
                            target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss>: “The President also has decided that the
                        United States should continue to give general support to the concept of
                        Mutual and Balanced Force Reductions in Europe. Further studies of <gloss
                            target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss>, both within the <gloss target="#t_US1"
                            >U.S.</gloss> Government and in <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>,
                        will be necessary to provide a realistic evaluation of approaches
                        (particularly asymmetrical force package approaches) to <gloss
                            target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss> which would operate to maintain or
                        enhance <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>’s military security relative
                        to the Warsaw Pact. Until these studies have been completed by the
                        Verification Panel and reviewed by the President, the <gloss target="#t_US1"
                            >U.S.</gloss> shall assume no commitments as to specific elements of a
                        formal <gloss target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss> proposals or agreement.” The
                        full text of <gloss target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss> 95 is scheduled for
                        publication in <ref target="frus1969-76v41">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1969–1976, volume XLI, Western
                            Europe; <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>, 1969–1972</ref>.</note>
                    that you wish to review positions to be taken by the United States at the
                    December 1970 <pb facs="0141" n="106" xml:id="pg_106"/>
                    <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> Ministerial meetings with respect to
                        <gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss> strategy and forces for <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>, and mutual and balanced force reductions
                        (<gloss target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss>).</p>
                <p>By separate memorandum (copy enclosed),<note n="3" xml:id="d40fn3">Attached but
                        not printed.</note> the Secretary has sent to you for approval a personal
                    message from you to the <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> Allies for use
                    during the forthcoming Ministerial meeting in stating the <gloss target="#t_US1"
                        >US</gloss> position on future <gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss> force
                    levels in Europe and on the Alliance’s study on defense problems for the
                    1970’s.</p>
                <p>Concerning <gloss target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss>, the Secretary plans to take the
                    following approach, looking toward further probes by the Allies of Soviet
                    interest in moving toward meaningful relaxation of tensions by again urging the
                    Warsaw Pact in the Ministerial Communiqué to join early East-West exploration of
                    possibilities for <gloss target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss>: <list>
                        <item>—note that the Warsaw Pact has finally responded to <gloss
                                target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>
                            <gloss target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss> Proposals by saying they were
                            prepared to discuss the reduction of “foreign armed forces” on the
                            territories of the European states, but that they are insisting such
                            talks come only after a <gloss target="#t_CES1">CES</gloss>.</item>
                        <item>—affirm <gloss target="#t_US1">US</gloss> concern that <gloss
                                target="#t_CES1">CES</gloss> would prove an unwieldy forum for any
                            eventual negotiations on <gloss target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss>, which is
                            why we have preferred to envisage discussions prior to <gloss
                                target="#t_CES1">CES</gloss> in a more limited framework, while not
                            ruling out eventual broader discussions.</item>
                        <item>—call for rejection by the Allies of the idea of discussing <gloss
                                target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss> only after a European Security
                            Conference and state that we should again urge Pact members to agree to
                            engage in exploratory <gloss target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss> talks next
                            year.</item>
                        <item>—if others favor this, concur that in the <gloss target="#t_MBFR1"
                                >MBFR</gloss> exploratory talks <gloss target="#t_NATO1"
                                >NATO</gloss> members should indicate a willingness for <gloss
                                target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss> negotiations initially to cover
                            stationed forces, and later embrace indigenous forces.<note n="4"
                                xml:id="d40fn4">On November 30, <persName corresp="#p_KHA1"
                                    >Kissinger</persName> responded in a memorandum to <persName
                                    corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName>: “The positions set forth
                                in your memorandum of November 27 relating to <gloss
                                    target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_CES1"
                                    >CES</gloss> have been reviewed in accordance with <gloss
                                    target="#t_NSDM1">NSDM</gloss> 95, and have been approved for
                                use at the Ministerial meeting.” (National Archives, <persName
                                    corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials,
                                    <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 260, Agency
                                Files, <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss>, <gloss
                                    target="#t_Vol1">Vol.</gloss> IX)</note>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">U. Alexis Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
